# ðŸŽ¬ Video Background Setup Guide

## Overview
This guide explains how to add and configure video backgrounds for the TechCare homepage hero section.

---

## Current Implementation

The homepage (`src/pages/Home.jsx`) uses the `VideoHeroBackground` component located at `src/components/VideoHeroBackground.jsx`.

### Current Configuration

```jsx
<VideoHeroBackground
    videoUrl="/videos/hero-background.mp4"
    posterUrl="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1581092160607-ee67c4ab602f?w=1920&q=80"
    opacity={0.5}
>
    {/* Hero content */}
</VideoHeroBackground>
```

---

## Adding Your Own Video

### Method 1: Local Video File (Recommended)

1. **Create videos directory**:
   ```bash
   mkdir public\videos
   ```

2. **Add your video file**:
   - Place your video file in `public/videos/`
   - Recommended name: `hero-background.mp4`
   - File path: `public/videos/hero-background.mp4`

3. **Video specifications** (recommended):
   - **Format**: MP4 (H.264 codec)
   - **Resolution**: 1920x1080 (Full HD) or 3840x2160 (4K)
   - **Duration**: 10-30 seconds (looped)
   - **File size**: Under 5MB for optimal loading
   - **Frame rate**: 30fps or 60fps
   - **Aspect ratio**: 16:9

4. **Optimize your video**:
   ```bash
   # Using FFmpeg to compress and optimize
   ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -vcodec h264 -acodec aac -vf scale=1920:1080 -b:v 1500k -b:a 128k public/videos/hero-background.mp4
   ```

### Method 2: External URL

Update the `videoUrl` prop in `src/pages/Home.jsx`:

```jsx
<VideoHeroBackground
    videoUrl="https://your-cdn.com/video.mp4"
    posterUrl="https://your-cdn.com/poster.jpg"
    opacity={0.5}
>
```

