## Component Configuration Options

### VideoHeroBackground Props:

```jsx
<VideoHeroBackground
    videoUrl="/videos/hero-background.mp4"    // Video file path or URL
    posterUrl="https://example.com/image.jpg" // Fallback image
    opacity={0.5}                             // Video overlay opacity (0-1)
>
    {children}                                 // Hero content
</VideoHeroBackground>
```

### Adjusting Opacity

- **0.3** - Very subtle, text highly visible
- **0.5** - Balanced (current setting)
- **0.7** - Strong overlay, video more visible

Update in `src/pages/Home.jsx`:
```jsx
opacity={0.5}  // Change this value
```

---

## Mobile Optimization

The component automatically:
- Pauses video on mobile devices (saves data)
- Shows poster image instead
- Disables autoplay on slow connections

---

## Performance Tips

### 1. Optimize Video Size
- Keep under 5MB for fast loading
- Use modern codecs (H.264, H.265)
- Consider WebM format for better compression

### 2. Lazy Loading
The video loads with `preload="auto"` - change to `preload="metadata"` for slower connections:

Edit `src/components/VideoHeroBackground.jsx`:
```jsx
<video
    ...
    preload="metadata"  // Instead of "auto"
/>
```

### 3. Content Delivery Network (CDN)
For production, host videos on a CDN:
- Cloudflare R2
- AWS S3 + CloudFront
- Bunny CDN
- Vercel Blob Storage

---

## Quick Start Commands

### Get a video from Pexels:
```bash
# 1. Visit https://www.pexels.com/videos/
# 2. Search for "technology circuit"
# 3. Download "Free Download" > "HD" or "Full HD"
# 4. Move to project:
mv ~/Downloads/video.mp4 public/videos/hero-background.mp4
```

### Optimize with FFmpeg:
```bash
# Install FFmpeg first: https://ffmpeg.org/download.html

# Compress and optimize
ffmpeg -i public/videos/hero-background.mp4 \
  -vcodec libx264 \
  -crf 28 \
  -preset slow \
  -vf scale=1920:1080 \
  -an \
  public/videos/hero-optimized.mp4

# Then rename
mv public/videos/hero-optimized.mp4 public/videos/hero-background.mp4
```

